#MEM id=dev source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/TOOLS.md
M|dev|Dev reads and writes mem via `/api/settings` — never directly to Supabase.
M|dev|**Read:**
M|dev|```
M|dev|GET /api/settings?type=mem&agentId=dev-lead&ventureId={activeVenture}
M|dev|```
M|dev|**Write:**
M|dev|```json
M|dev|POST /api/settings
M|dev|{
M|dev|"type": "mem",
M|dev|"agentId": "dev-lead",
M|dev|"ventureId": "{activeVenture}",
M|dev|"key": "architecture_decisions",
M|dev|"value": "SSE over WebSockets — simpler, works with Vercel serverless."
M|dev|}
M|dev|```
M|dev|After every POST: edit the Live State table in `mem.md` to match.
M|dev|Dev's primary tool for code rv, PR management, and tech debt tracking.
M|dev|**Use cases:**
M|dev|- rv open PRs from Raj and Mia before approving merge
M|dev|- Check recent commit history before starting a new phase
M|dev|- Create issues for identified tech debt or architectural notes
M|dev|- Verify what was merged before writing a new API contract
M|dev|- Check if a branch has CI failures before Quinn starts QA
M|dev|**Key operations:**
M|dev|```
M|dev|list_pull_requests    → see open PRs awaiting Dev rv
M|dev|get_pull_request      → read a specific PR's diff for rv
M|dev|list_issues           → check open tech debt and bug items
M|dev|create_issue          → log tech debt or architectural decisions as trackable issues
M|dev|get_commit            → verify what changed before a handoff
M|dev|```
M|dev|Dev uses Supabase to verify that the schema matches what's in the code.
M|dev|**Use cases:**
M|dev|- Inspect current table structure to verify migrations ran correctly
M|dev|- Check that new columns exist before deploying code that references them
M|dev|- Verify RLS (Row Level sec) policies are in place
M|dev|- Cross-check `agents` table contents after a seed script runs
M|dev|- Confirm Raj's schema decisions are reflected in the live database
M|dev|**Key operations:**
M|dev|```
M|dev|list_tables           → verify all tables exist in public schema
M|dev|describe_table        → check column names, types, constraints
M|dev|execute_query         → spot-check data integrity (read-only verification)
M|dev|```
M|dev|| Route | Method | When |
M|dev||-------|--------|------|
M|dev|| `/api/settings` | GET | ses start — read own mem keys |
M|dev|| `/api/settings` | POST | After any architecture dec to write to mem |
M|dev|| `/api/vtr` | GET | To confirm active vtr ctx before writing API contracts |
M|dev|Dev does not call data routes (`/api/instagram`, `/api/anl`, etc.) — those are Raj's territory. Dev calls them only if debugging a systemic architecture issue.
M|dev|| Tool | Purpose | Status |
M|dev||------|---------|--------|
M|dev|| Vercel MCP | Check dpl status, build logs, function timeouts | Planned |
M|dev|| Linear MCP | Track engineering milestones and tech debt in Linear | Planned |